# JavaScript Class Structure

```javascript
class Animal {
    constructor(name, age) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }

    speak() {
        console.log(`${this.name} makes a noise.`);
    }
}

const dog = new Animal('Rex', 5);
dog.speak();  // Outputs: Rex makes a noise.
```

### Class Diagram

