```

In the diagram above, a class 'Animal' includes properties for 'name' and 'age', and a method 'speak()'. Instances of 'Animal' inherit from the base 'Object' class.

# Inheritance in JavaScript Classes

```javascript
class Dog extends Animal {
    constructor(name, age, breed) {
        super(name, age);
        this.breed = breed;
    }

    speak() {
        console.log(`${this.name} barks.`);
    }
}

const beagle = new Dog('Buddy', 3, 'Beagle');
beagle.speak();  // Outputs: Buddy barks.
```

### Inheritance Diagram

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class Animal {
        -name: String
        -age: Number
        +speak()
    }

    class Dog {
        -breed: String
        +speak()
    }

    Animal <|-- Dog
```

This diagram depicts the inheritance relationship, where 'Dog' extends 'Animal', inheriting its properties while modifying the 'speak()' method.

# Static Methods in JavaScript Classes

```javascript
class Calculator {
    static add(a, b) {
        return a + b;
    }

    static subtract(a, b) {
        return a - b;
    }
}

console.log(Calculator.add(5, 3));  // Outputs: 8
console.log(Calculator.subtract(10, 7));  // Outputs: 3
```

